{{merge|PlusEnergy|date=November 2018|discuss=Talk:PlusEnergy#Merge}} [[File:Freiburg 071ss.jpg|thumb|'''Energy-plus-house'''s at [[Vauban, Freiburg|Freiburg-Vauban]] in Germany]] [[File:Plus-energie-haus-ffm-033.jpg|thumb|Prototype in Germany]] An '''energy-plus house''' (also called: Plus-Energy House, Efficiency-Plus House) produces more energy from [[renewable energy]] sources, over the course of a year, than it imports from external sources. This is achieved using a combination of [[microgeneration]] technology and [[low-energy building]] techniques, such as: [[passive solar building design]], [[Building insulation|insulation]] and careful site selection and placement. A reduction of [[modern conveniences]] can also contribute to energy savings, however many energy-plus houses are almost indistinguishable from a traditional home, preferring instead to use highly energy-efficient appliances, fixtures, etc., throughout the house.
