A '''partially disclosed principal''' is one whose agent reveals that he has a principal, but does not reveal the principal's identity. This concept has important implications in liability law. It is in contrast to a [[disclosed principal]] and [[undisclosed principal]].<ref>Bohlman, 2001, {{ISBN|978-0-324-06183-3}}</ref>

