The [http://codex.stanford.edu Stanford Center for Computers and the Law] - CodeX - is an interdisciplinary [https://web.archive.org/web/20061013065512/http://codex.stanford.edu/background.html computer science and law] research center jointly operated by [[Stanford Law School]] and the [[Stanford School of Engineering]] through the [http://cs.stanford.edu/ Department of Computer Science.]

[http://codex.stanford.edu CodeX's] mission is to employ a multidisciplinary approach to addressing problems in the law by applying computer science technologies, methods, and theories to legal problems.

